cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.NE 

This paper discusses deep reinforcement learning algorithms and their applications in robotics and visual understanding. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also mentions the application of DRL in robotics, which suggests cs.RO (Robotics) as a likely sub-category. Finally, the use of deep neural networks in DRL algorithms suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as a possible sub-category.
